text.section:
The Secretary shall:
Develop a system to gather and maintain data;
Develop methods to:
Contact parents or guardians of newborns and their identified primary care providers regarding the results of the newborn hearing screening;
Contact parents or guardians of hearing-impaired infants and infants who have a risk factor of developing a hearing impairment; and
Refer the parents or guardians to appropriate services;
Establish a telephone hot line to communicate information about hearing impairment and services for hearing-impaired infants;
Appoint an Advisory Council for the program;
Meet annually with the Advisory Council; and
In consultation with the Advisory Council, adopt rules and regulations necessary to implement the program.
